HEADWORD: Chih fu
<hw>Chih" fu`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Chin. <ets>chih fu</ets>,
lit., (He who) knows (the) prefecture.]</ety> <def>An official
administering a prefecture of China; a prefect, supervising the civil
business of the hsiens or districts comprised in his fu (which
see).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

